<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Anderson Sets AL Beaning Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- Brady Anderson set an American League record  
tonight by getting hit by a pitch twice in the same inning, and he 
scored twice during the Baltimore Orioles' 10-run first inning 
against the Texas Rangers. 
</P>
<P>
	Anderson, the Orioles' leadoff hitter, was hit twice in the  
first inning by Texas pitcher Mike Morgan. Manager Johnny Oates 
removed Morgan after Anderson was hit for the second time. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the third time in modern history that a player has been  
hit by a pitch twice in the same inning. Willard Schmidt of the 
Cincinnati Reds did it on April 26, 1959, and Frank Thomas of the 
New York Mets was hit twice on April 29, 1962. 
</P>
<P>
	Anderson scored the first time on a sacrifice fly and came in  
the second time on a three-run double by Mike Bordick. 
</P>
<P>
	Anderson has been been hit by a pitch eight times this season,  
high on the Orioles. 
</P>
<P>
	The 10-run inning tied an Oriole record, reached three times  
previously, the last time on Aug. 21, 1985, against Seattle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
