<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Kingston Won't Watch Fiennes' Films </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- ``ER'' star Alex Kingston won't watch former  
husband Ralph Fiennes' movies because the experience would be ``too 
painful.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Fiennes left Ms. Kingston after 11 years, including two years of  
marriage, for actress Francesca Annis. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've got no idea what Ralph is up to,'' the British actress  
told Radio Times magazine. ``I won't see his work ever again. It 
would be too painful to watch 90 minutes of his face on screen.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Kingston, who remarried recently, said she wants to have  
children and is confident the writers of ``ER'' could cope with a 
pregnancy. She plays Dr. Elizabeth Corday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Either they'd write it in or I'll wear scrubs for nine months  
because they're so big they make you look pregnant,'' she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
