<HEADLINE> Cops: Mom Tried Selling Child on Net </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LITTLETON, Colo. (AP) -- A woman was arrested on suspicion of  
trying to sell her 8-year-old adopted Russian daughter for $4,000 
through an e-mail, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Denise K. Thomas was arrested Friday for investigation for  
criminal attempted trafficking in children and released, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	``What she was really trying to do was set up a private adoption  
to avoid the bureaucracy and regulations required around that 
issue. But yes, the bottom line was she was trying to sell the 
child,'' said Undersheriff Grayson Robinson. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Thomas, 42, who is married and lives with her husband and  
biological 14-year-old son, denied the charge. 
</P>
<P>
	``I had no intention of selling a child or anything like that,''  
Mrs. Thomas said in an interview with KWGN-TV on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``For whatever reason they've blown this thing way out of  
proportion, not even bothered to interview us.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The girl had not been abused, Robinson said. She was placed in a  
foster home. 
</P>
<P>
	The proposed sale was uncovered Friday when sheriff's deputies  
were contacted by a Texas couple who said they had received an 
e-mail from a woman offering to sell the girl in a ``private 
adoption.'' 
</P>
