<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Elbow Sidelined Indians' Reed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- Cleveland Indians reliever Steve Reed, second  
on the team with 20 appearances this season, was hospitalized 
Monday with an infected bursar sac in his left elbow. 
</P>
<P>
	Reed was being held overnight at Cleveland's Lutheran Hospital  
where his elbow was being treated with antibiotics. 
</P>
<P>
	The right-hander is 1-0 with a 1.93 ERA this year. Last season,  
Reed, acquired in a July trade from San Francisco, was limited to 
just six appearances in September after a blood clot in his right 
wrist caused numbness in the fingers of his right hand. 
</P>
<P>
	Reed, signed in April to a two-year contract extension, is the  
latest Indians reliever to be sidelined. Paul Shuey and Ricky 
Rincon recently rejoined the team after spending time on the 15-day 
disabled list. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
