<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Student Arrested in Toy Gun Threat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- A special education student who told police  
he pointed a cap gun at a girl in school to scare her was charged 
Monday with assault, terroristic threats and weapons possession. 
</P>
<P>
	Police moved all 630 students of William H. Brown Academy into  
the cafeteria for three hours to find the 13-year-old boy after 
learning he pointed a gun at the girl as she walked into class, 
police spokesman Matt Greimel said. 
</P>
<P>
	The girl didn't tell anyone about the incident for two hours and  
the boy had left school before police were called. 
</P>
<P>
	Police never found the weapon, which the boy said he gave to a  
friend, Greimel said. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy, whose name was not released because he is a juvenile,  
may have had a crush on the 13-year-old girl, Greimel said. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy, charged in juvenile court, was expected to be  
transferred to a juvenile facility. 
</P>
<P>
	He is a special-needs student with emotional problems, but he is  
not learning-disabled, district spokeswoman Michelle Baldwin said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
