<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Avis To Buy Cendant Fleet Managment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GARDEN CITY, N.Y. (AP) -- Avis Rent A Car Inc. is buying the auto  
fleet leasing and fuel card businesses from Cendant Corp. for about 
$1.8 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Avis officials said the deal announced today will help the  
nation's second biggest auto rental firm expand and diversify its 
commercial rental business, including gaining a foothold in Europe. 
</P>
<P>
	Avis, based in Garden City, is buying Cendant's PHH and Wright  
Express divisions. 
</P>
<P>
	``PHH and Avis are a natural fit, since both companies  
principally serve corporate clients and there are a number of 
opportunities to cross-market to each other's customers,'' Avis 
executive vice president and chief financial officer Kevin Sheehan 
said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Cendant vice president Stephen Holmes said the deal represents a  
step in the formerly Parsippany, N.J.-based franchise giant's 
strategic realignment. It also provides Cendant, which is now based 
in New York, with a much-needed infusion of cash. 
</P>
<P>
	Cendant controls 20 percent of Avis, which it spun off in 1997.  
</P>
<P>
	PHH provides vehicle services to 19,000 companies in North  
America and Europe. Its total worldwide fleet exceeds 700,000 
vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
	Wright Express provides fuel management services to commercial  
clients. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal has resulted from an auction process among several  
bidders. Avis officials said they expect to close the transaction 
by June 30. 
</P>
<P>
	Avis will finance the deal through a combination of debt and  
preferred stock. 
</P>
<P>
	PHH and Wright Express will remain separate and operate under  
the leadership of their current management teams, Avis president 
and chief operating officer F. Robert Salerno said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Their contributions will bring us closer to our vision of  
becoming the world's leading provider of full service automotive 
transportation and vehicle management solutions,'' Salerno said. 
</P>
<P>
	Avis also is acquiring two PHH subsidiaries, Cendant Business  
Answers (Europe) PLC and the Harpur Group Ltd. Both are leading 
vehicle services providers in the United Kingdom. 


</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
