<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Stocks End Down; Dow Off 174.61  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks fell sharply today as investors shed  
Internet and bank shares, fearing that profits will be hampered in 
coming months by threats as diverse as higher interest rates and 
the Year 2000 bug. The Dow Jones industrial average was down 
174.61, or by 1.6 percent, at 10,654.67. At one point late in the 
session, the blue-chip average had tumbled almost 203 points. After 
several listless sessions on Wall Street, investors seized upon 
some industry analysts' warnings as a catalyst for a selloff. Broad 
measures were also lower. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 fell 23.64 to 
1,306.65, and the Nasdaq composite fell 66.54 to 2,453.60. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
