<HEADLINE> Seton Scholl, LIG Agree to Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Seton Scholl Healthcare PLC, maker of Dr. Scholl  
brand footcare products, is buying condom and surgical glove maker 
London International Group PLC for about $1 billion in stock. 
</P>
<P>
	Seton Scholl will hold a 56 percent stake in the new group, to  
be named SSL International. 
</P>
<P>
	Seton Scholl shares rose 4 percent in midday trading Monday  
while LIG shares were down 3 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The two companies said they expected the merger to lead to  
improved earnings and cost savings. 
</P>
<P>
	The combined group would have had pro-forma sales in 1989 of 642  
million pounds, or $1.04 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Seton Scholl, based in Knutsford, Cheshire, was formed last year  
in a merger between Seton Healthcare PLC and Scholl PLC. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to surgical gloves, London-based LIG makes Durex  
brand condoms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
