<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rogers &AMP; Wells, UK Law Firm to Merge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The leaders of the New York-based law firm  
Rogers &AMP; Wells have decided to merge with one of Britain's biggest 
and most prestigious firms, Clifford Chance. 
</P>
<P>
	The executive committees of the two firms voted separately late  
Friday to submit proposals for a merger to their partners, a senior 
attorney at one of the firms said today. 
</P>
<P>
	If approved by the full partnerships it would be the first  
merger of major U.S. and British law firms. 
</P>
<P>
	A spokeswoman for Rogers &AMP; Wells, Jolie Goldstein, declined to  
comment. 
</P>
<P>
	The senior attorney, who would speak only on condition of  
anonymity, said, ``There are some conflicts that need to be 
resolved before we can make any kind of announcement. The executive 
committees of the two firms have voted to submit proposals to merge 
to the partners.'' 
</P>
<P>
	If completed, the merger is expected to spark similar unions  
between firms in the two countries amid a trend of consolidation in 
the increasingly international field of law. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal would create a combined firm to be known in the United  
States as Clifford Chance Rogers &AMP; Wells and simply as Clifford 
Chance elsewhere, and would take effect Jan. 1, 2000. 
</P>
<P>
	Clifford Chance has 2,000 lawyers and a large international  
network of offices. The 400 attorneys at Rogers &AMP; Wells would give 
it a strong U.S. base. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
