<HEADLINE> Russian Co. To Drill for Oil in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOSCOW (AP) -- A joint Russian-Belarus oil company has signed a  
contract to drill and service oil wells in Iran, the ITAR-Tass news 
agency reported Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The company, Slavneft, will develop the wells in Iran's Ahway  
Province, the report said. It added that if the contract was 
satisfactorily fulfilled, it could lead to a major contract for 
further work in Iran. 
</P>
<P>
	The contract was signed by Slavneft's president, Vasily Duma,  
and Heidar Bahmani, managing director of the National Iranian 
Drilling Co. The report did not say when the deal was concluded or 
its total value. 
</P>
