<HEADLINE> England's Rugby Captain Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Lawrence Dallaglio resigned as England's rugby  
union captain on Monday following allegations that he had used and 
sold drugs. 
</P>
<P>
	The decision was announced by the English Rugby Football Union  
after a three-hour meeting with Dallaglio. 
</P>
<P>
	English rugby was shocked Sunday when the tabloids News of the  
World newspaper published the drug allegations. 
</P>
<P>
	``I used to be a drug dealer,'' the newspaper quoted Dallaglio  
as saying. ``I made big, big money from dealing in drugs. That's 
how I used to make money before I took up rugby.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The paper said Dallaglio, 26, admitted taking ecstasy and  
cocaine at a party after the British Lions' 2-1 series win over 
South Africa in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
