<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mets Call Up Pitcher Isringhausen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Starting pitcher Bobby Jones was placed on the  
15-day disabled list by the New York Mets on Monday and 
right-hander Jason Isringhausen was called up from the minors and 
thrown right into the rotation. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones, 3-3 with a 5.81 ERA, has a strained right shoulder. He  
was knocked out in the third inning of his last start against 
Philadelphia on Saturday and has not won since April 17. He went on 
the DL effective Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Isringhausen, who was to start against Pittsburgh on Monday  
night, was pitching in the major leagues for the first time since 
Sept. 23, 1997. He missed last season while recovering from his 
third arm surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	This year, he was 3-1 with a 2.53 ERA in eight starts with  
Norfolk of the International League. He also had 47 strikeouts in 
46 1-3 innings and had allowed only 32 hits. 
</P>
<P>
	He had a standout rookie season in 1995, going 9-2 with a 2.81  
ERA. 
</P>
<P>
	After that, he had surgery on his right shoulder and elbow in  
1996 and the elbow again in January 1998. In between, he broke his 
right wrist and was diagnosed with tuberculosis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
