<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-24 22:51:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> `Phantom' Can't Beat the Dinosaurs / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The ``Star Wars'' prequel has nothing to be  
ashamed of when it comes to box office numbers. 
</P>
<P>
	``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace'' amassed $64.8  
million Friday through Sunday -- well short of the $72.1 million for 
``The Lost World: Jurassic Park'' over the Memorial Day weekend in 
1997, according to figures released Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The ``Star Wars'' numbers still set records (a five-day gross of  
$105.7 million and $28.5 million on opening day). It also became 
the fastest movie to break the $100 million barrier, in just five 
days. 
</P>
<P>
	The only other big movie opening last weekend was ``The Love  
Letter,'' which had a disappointing $2.7 million for fifth place 
despite being billed as a romantic alternative. 
</P>
<P>
	``The Mummy,'' meanwhile, stayed strong enough to also break  
$100 million, collecting $13.8 million to finish second. 
``Entrapment'' was third with $6.3 million and ``The Matrix'' 
fourth with $2.9 million. 
</P>
<P>
	In art houses, ``Tea With Mussolini'' continued to do well,  
grossing $1.3 million. It dropped only 22 percent in its second 
week. 
</P>
<P>
	The top 20 movies at North American theaters Friday through  
Sunday, followed by distributing studio, gross, number of theater 
locations, average receipts per location, total gross and number of 
weeks in release, as compiled by Exhibitor Relations Co. Inc. and 
ACNielsen EDI Inc.: 
</P>
<P>
	1. ``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace,'' 20th Century  
Fox, $64.8 million, 2,970 locations, $21,822 average, $105.7 
million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	2. ``The Mummy,'' Universal, $13.8 million, 3,276 locations,  
$4,210 average, $100.2 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	3. ``Entrapment,'' 20th Century Fox, $6.3 million, 2,869  
locations, $2,200 average, $59.9 million, four weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	4. ``The Matrix,'' Warner Bros., $2.9 million, 2,521 locations,  
$1,141 average, $149.5 million, eight weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	5. ``The Love Letter,'' DreamWorks, $2.7 million, 769 locations,  
$3,502 average, $2.7 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	6. ``William Shakespeare's A Midsummer Night's Dream,'' Fox  
Searchlight, $2.6 million, 1,093 locations, $2,387 average, $8.2 
million, two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	7. ``Never Been Kissed,'' Fox, $1.7 million, 1,888 locations,  
$924 average, $46.2 million, seven weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	8. ``Black Mask,'' Artisan, $1.66 million, 988 locations, $1,686  
average, $7.3 million, two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	9. ``Life,'' Universal, $1.6 million, 1,720 locations, $910  
average, $57.5 million, six weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	10. ``Election,'' Paramount, $1.5 million, 827 locations, $1,783  
average, $9.2 million, five weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	11. ``Trippin','' Rogue, $1.4 million, 781 locations, $1,811  
average, $5.2 million, two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	12. ``Tea with Mussolini,'' MGM, $1.3 million, 273 locations,  
$4,692 average, $3.6 million, two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	13. ``Shakespeare in Love,'' Miramax, $745,400, 1,223 locations,  
$609 average, $95.9 million, 24 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	14. ``Analyze This,'' Warner Bros., $629,481, 1,123 locations,  
$561 average, $103.1 million, 12 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	15. ``10 Things I Hate About You,'' Disney, $584,961, 981  
locations, $596 average, $34.6 million, eight weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	16. ``Cookie's Fortune,'' October, $460,326, 504 locations, $913  
average, $9.2 million, eight weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	17. ``Life is Beautiful,'' Miramax, $414,662, 579 locations,  
$716 average, $55.8 million, 31 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	18. ``Payback,'' Paramount, $330,249, 567 locations, $582  
average, $80.5 million, 16 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	19. ``Forces of Nature,'' DreamWorks, $283,628, 558 locations,  
$509 average, $51.4 million, 10 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	20. ``The Out-of-Towners,'' Paramount, $273,153, 802 locations,  
$341 average, $27.3 million, eight weeks. 
</P>
