</P>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Former Sen. Bill Bradley, Al Gore's sole rival  
for the Democratic presidential nomination, is considering 
including a ban on the sale of handguns in an aggressive gun 
control plan that he will unveil later in his campaign. Bradley 
already has endorsed a ``handgun card'' -- a photo identity card 
required of anybody carrying a handgun. Bradley said he also would 
seek to ban the possession of handguns by minors. 

