<P>
	Death of Wrestler Probed  
</P>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Investigators are searching for clues  
into the cause of an accident that killed wrestling star Owen Hart. 
Hart, who was wrestling under the name the ``Blue Blazer,'' died 
last night when he fell 50 feet into the ring during a pre-fight 
stunt. Some witnesses say his cable snapped during the stunt, 
others think Hart became disconnected from the cable. ``From the 
information we have so far, it had something to do with the harness 
system,'' police said. Hart, a Canadian, was a member of a famous 
wrestling family. 

</P>
<P>
	Da Vinci Masterpiece Is Restored  
</P>
<P>
	ROME (AP) -- After two decades, the restoration of Leonardo da  
Vinci's ``The Last Supper'' on a Milan monastery wall is finished, 
with experts promising that the masterpiece has regained ``life and 
light.'' A private, VIP-only ceremony Thursday night in the dining 
hall of the Basilica of St. Mary of the Graces will give the first 
viewing of the completed restoration of Leonardo's Renaissance 
depiction of Christ's last meal with his apostles. The exhibit 
opens to the public Friday. 

</P>
<P>
	Connecticut Co. Trying To Clone Pets  
</P>
<P>
	FARMINGTON, Conn. (AP) -- Two entrepreneurs are charging pet  
owners to store their beloved animals' DNA in anticipation of the 
day when science can clone Fido or Fluffy. For $1,000 per pet -- 
plus a $100 annual storage fee -- PerPETuate Inc. will take a 
genetic sample from a living or dead animal and keep it frozen at 
their lab. 

</P>
<P>
	Dow Ends Down 174.61  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks staged a sharp and broad retreat today  
amid weakness in Internet and bank shares as investors waited to 
see if inflation is threatening the vibrant U.S. economy. The Dow 
Jones industrial average ended at 10,654.67, down 174.61. On the 
NYSE, losers led gainers 2,042-947. The Nasdaq was at 2,453.64, 
down 66.50. 

</P>
