	Tyson Is Released From Jail  
</P>
<P>
	ROCKVILLE, Md. (AP) -- Mike Tyson was released today from a  
Maryland jail after serving 3 1/2 months on a one-year assault 
sentence. The former heavyweight champion was released based on an 
Indiana judge's decision to end his probation for a 1992 rape 
conviction. Tyson was granted parole in Maryland on Friday. But 
Indiana needed to approve the release before Tyson could go home 
for the first time since he was sentenced Feb. 5. 

</P>
<P>
	AP NewsBrief by JEROME MINERVA  
