<HEADLINE> Charges Filed Against Shriver Aide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- A personal assistant to Eunice Kennedy  
Shriver was in jail Monday on charges he used a computer in her 
home to e-mail child pornography. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas Jared Pearl, 39, of Potomac, Md., was arrested Friday as  
he stepped off a plane with plans to visit a 12-year-old girl he 
met through an Internet chat line, according to a federal complaint 
filed Monday. The girl actually was an adult Customs Service 
informant. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Shriver is a sister of the late President John F. Kennedy  
and mother of NBC News' Maria Shriver. Pearl, who had worked for 
the Shrivers since October, was fired after the family learned of 
the allegations, Kennedy family spokesman Robert Corcoran said. 
</P>
<P>
	Pearl allegedly wrote sexually explicit messages and transmitted  
pictures depicting adult-child sexual relations. 
</P>
<P>
	The complaint said Pearl claimed to live in Mrs. Shriver's home,  
but Corcoran would not say whether that was true. 
</P>
<P>
	In federal court Monday, Pearl asked for a lawyer to be  
appointed for him. 
</P>
