<HEADLINE> A&AMP;L, Bank of Ireland Talk Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Alliance &AMP; Leicester PLC and Bank of Ireland Group  
confirmed Monday that they are discussing a merger. 
</P>
<P>
	The combined group would be the eighth largest bank in Britain  
and the fifth largest mortgage provider, and No. 1 in Ireland with 
assets of $103 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Based on 1998 results, two companies had profits before  
exceptional items of $1.6 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	The companies said they are discussing dual-listed company  
structure, with Alliance &AMP; Leicester and Bank of Ireland 
shareholders retaining their existing holdings in the respective 
companies. 
</P>
<P>
	The banks estimate the merger would create pretax cost savings  
of more than $320 million. 
</P>
