<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-24 15:12:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Monday on the New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Stock Market, 
and American Stock Exchange. 

</P>
<P>
 *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Avis Rent A Car Inc. fell 7 3/8 to 28  
</P>
<P>
 *Cendant rose 11/16 to 19 7/8 
</P>
<P>
	Avis is buying Cendant's auto fleet leasing and fuel card  
businesses for about $1.8 billion. Cendant is trying to strip down 
to its core businesses as it works to recover from an 
accounting-fraud scandal that battered its stock price last year. 

</P>
<P>
 *Telecom Italia fell 9 13/16 to 99 3/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Former typewriter maker Olivetti won a heated battle for Telecom  
Italia this weekend, acquiring a stake of almost 52 percent. The 
deal clears the way for a complete takeover of Telecom Italia, a 
deal estimated at $64 billion. 

</P>
<P>
 *AK Steel Holding Corp. rose 2 1/16 to 24 7/16    	
</P>
<P>
	AK Steel, an integrated steelmaker, agreed to acquire Armco Inc.  
for $842 million. The two companies used to be one; in recent 
years, AK has primarily been a carbon steelmaker, while Armco has 
made stainless and other specialty steels. 

</P>
<P>
 *Resortquest Intl. fell 6 1/8 to 8 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Resortquest, which rents resort properties, said it expects  
second-quarter earnings to miss analysts' expectations by 4 cents 
to 8 cents per share. The company cited increased growth and 
acquisition expenses. 

</P>
<P>
 *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Motorcar Parts &AMP; Accessories Inc. fell 4 to 7    	
</P>
<P>
	The company said it expects a significant loss for the fourth  
quarter of its fiscal year, which ended March 31, 1999. Motorcar 
Parts, a maker of alternators and starters for cars, added that it 
may post a loss for the whole year. 

</P>
<P>
 *CustomTracks Corp. rose 15 1/16 to 76    	
</P>
<P>
	An analyst at Joseph Charles &AMP; Associates set a price target of  
$230 for CustomTracks, a developer of Internet-based payment 
systems. The company plans to introduce a new security device for 
Internet transactions in August. 

</P>
<P>
 *Syntel Inc. rose 2 1/16 to 12 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Business Week called Syntel a ``hot growth'' company in its May  
31 edition that hit newsstands Friday. Syntel is an 
information-technology consulting company. 

</P>
<P>
 *Texas Micro rose 1 1/4 to 6 1/8    	
</P>
<P>
	RadiSys Corp. will acquire Texas Micro, another communications  
technology company, for about $115 million in stock. 


</P>
</TEXT>
