<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar, Gold Both Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was down against most other major  
currencies in European trading Monday. Gold fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0574, up from $1.0563 Friday.  
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates compared with late Friday: 123.82 Japanese  
yen, down from 124.00; 1.5147 Swiss francs, down from 1.5177; and 
1.4582 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4584 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.5961, down from $1.6033.  
</P>
<P>
	Midday in New York, the dollar bought 123.64 yen, while the euro  
was worth $1.0572 and the pound traded at $1.5938. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar was worth: 1.8497 German marks, down from 1.8516; 
6.2035 French francs, down from 6.2099; 2.0841 Dutch guilders, down 
from 2.0863; and 1,831.16 Italian lire, down from 1,833.07. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $271.80 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$272.60 on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Zurich was closed for a holiday.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold fell $2.70 in Hong Kong to close at $272.35.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.06 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$5.22. 
</P>
</TEXT>
